<subSubSection id="BAB60C0951CC07A988F47C1CEE4D578B" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="35D1A5015CA228B1B53D66AFBDAB6BF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DBFF53B66E603668CB7099F46A054D72" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
The only species of 
<taxonomicName id="4071C1E1CE790FD2BFDDA896587E7EC1" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="782EBB51F104CCB90F8036ADA0C9AD9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following combination of characters: body longer than 3.5 mm; femora and tibiae with spines scattered along their length; femora distinctly yellow basally and dark brown distally, tibiae dark brown with subapical pale bands; wing with a single radial cell and spermathecae unequal in size and without necks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5C2CD081962C93296E6F9D9BAEE0E6C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph id="C06A20C2646882AD59846E3D6AC1DB60" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A48CFAA0305E8C8D1873EFF14DEA617" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="24E157E06DD13117A42CC12271D30512" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
Female. 
<emphasis id="10047F321D4CDC1228D56FD14D161BB8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Body</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="43882E56C7563B4ADB40EF0F1AC7746D" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) 4.25 (3.85-4.28) mm in length. Wing 2.69 (2.69-2.95) mm in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B2D9C4C8027EC7197FF3C0ABE9C723D" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="8264C43AC2EAFDD5BE631549E1F90B7E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="14D34811B9ADE26FF9C7D8A7B0A45E84" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Head dark brown</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Eyes contiguous, bare (
<figureCitation id="4B93D8217E8DDD7C7CC8A0B23B837D67" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Antenna dark brown with slightly paler pedicel, basal flagellomeres short and stout, distal 5 flagellomeres each much longer than basal 8 flagellomeres, lengths in ratio of 96:47:47:46:51:50:58:64:129:123:127:111:140; AR 1.37 (1.17-1.37, 
<emphasis id="813D6C0603CB15E010BD0CE709530CA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 5) (
<figureCitation id="EAE03CA5FE3C29C110CC89360682BCD4" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpi brown, 5-segmented, third segment long, not distinctly swollen, a few scattered hyaline sensillae preapically, lengths in ratio of 17:33:86:43:42, PR 3.07 (2.99-3.44) (
<figureCitation id="1D0746A6385D2F69DB5D69CDE97226C9" captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="3867DDD3EBE3F0503082AE993119709B" captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">16</figureCitation>
). Mandible with seven coarse teeth (
<figureCitation id="76ECEA551F0950663F44378F9C8FD0C5" captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="112BD54D222549D52D1194446AB9AD4E" captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="506BFFADE387A7F5FFD86AA76BE0AD3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="DAFBF89359B980FB906E254811E60222" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="DC1E3AE02F1F89293197FF8621C4F8AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Scutum dark brown, some specimens with humeral area slightly paler, with fine microsetae and several bristles near base of wings. Scutellum and postscutellum concolourous with scutum. Coxae dark brown, trochanters light brown; forefemur, midfemur with basal 2/3 yellow and distal 1/3 dark brown, basal 1/3 of hind femur yellow, distal 2/3 dark brown; basal 1/2 of fore tibia and mid tibia dark brown, distal 1/2 yellow, except narrow dark apex; 2/3 of hind tibia dark brown, apical 1/3 slightly paler, dark apex (
<figureCitation id="D235D2767016CF8C640BF1CBB0FBD220" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="351F2074D3E36D5B620EE1455D71F5BA" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">5-7</figureCitation>
). All femora and tibiae with many scattered black spines over their entire length, variable in number; hind tibial comb (
<figureCitation id="FA7DE5FEE216AE66B60CE407B2C55948" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with nine spines. Tarsomeres 
<normalizedToken id="81D971E27E0715F99AD69BDC5D1E3EA7" originalValue="I–IV">I-IV</normalizedToken>
yellow except brown apices; tarsomere V entirely dark brown; foretarsomere and hindtarsomere 
<normalizedToken id="F5B219517870AF3E72C45293FEC3F34B" originalValue="I–II">I-II</normalizedToken>
and midtarsomere III each with single apical spine, midtarsomere 
<normalizedToken id="48320AC6BA3D940C41ADBC505760E808" originalValue="I–II">I-II</normalizedToken>
with two apical spines, midtarsomere I also with a basal spine, foretarsomere and hind tarsomere III and tarsomere IV of all legs without apical spine, tarsomere V (
<figureCitation id="5552AB1FD3BFE79AC985A8B20F8CD2D9" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with 14 ventral batonnets; claws equal, 0.8 times the length of tarsomere V and bearing two strong basal teeth on the outer surface ca. 0.3 times of length of claw (
<figureCitation id="BDF1CCCCDEB252EC69B1818F32CD3F84" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9F475550E288B8A873E1287CFBA4CC60" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">4</figureCitation>
). RL-L 1013:948:377:196:142:80:245 and TR 1.92 (1.78-2.08, 
<emphasis id="C92DA2FA10DDDABD95EB1CB584559DA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 5) in fore leg, RL-L 1460:1080:533:231:173:91:225 and TR 2.30 (2.15-2.56, 
<emphasis id="2C75409A7F9A470B1BDE219A0B464F57" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 5) in mid leg, RL-L 1508:1269:1000:320:236:133:240 and TR 3.10 (2.90-3.10, 
<emphasis id="563A74A7C736BA7DB8AA0D5E45CC0767" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 5) in hind leg. Wing membrane pale grey, CR 0.82 (0.81-0.82, 
<emphasis id="A96DA9808639F2A61FF1A2EA8EEC112B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 5), a single radial cell (
<figureCitation id="0DC847B2EEA9BFC4DCE3DACF88CC15CE" captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Haltere white.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3FD58F56F7184122988909FB7CD6A749" doi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" start="Figures 1–11" startId="F1">
