<subSubSection id="E0FD7AA5D5172D7FE8798A4E99B39594" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="97B27275BA76345C552895F94053EBC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820F856094AE559063F6161E599FDEBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="3D914ABEF8CC5C647A21999F8D57EAC2" lsidName="bamenwana" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="096D25B43F977A7467F89DE323EF0327" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the collecting location of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="346DDBB87D62549B02768D66F7BDDDD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3E46AF95902BAB5A16740ABF9CF38C93" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C50BF117DB1B55869E19E52965AF242" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Known only from the Bamenwan mangrove forest of Hainan Prov., China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FED5DBA00EA9812B022178E6C250970A" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0DA00F3D4E80BC0D99F0FEBB8DF69392" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B0FE6AD08D99CAA767E201E2EFDCA58" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
Female specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="0CDCC284B2FFF4685CAF845AB61378D7" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia bamenwana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="49C42541943A266658939FD5AD54BF06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
run to genus 
<taxonomicName id="716066C3145220A25506103837BC77FA" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C70838C8E2B09BBF91CBCEBE3ACD1CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="AD19A79B6420A2743090E34963685D39" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1051/parasite/1974495595" author="Wirth, WW" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Parasitologie (Paris)" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="595 - 613" refId="B11" refString="Wirth, WW, Ratanaworabhan, NC, Blanton, FS, 1974. Synopsis of the genera of Ceratopogonidae (Diptera). Annales de Parasitologie (Paris) 49: 595 - 613" title="Synopsis of the genera of Ceratopogonidae (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/parasite/1974495595" volume="49" year="1974">Wirth et al. (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and conforms to the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="394F94B7E4BEFEDE92893FE38A8595A7" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A9A2F23A2CAEF61E705571B831DE3739" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="D1BFBE8D6B4B11A832AB986E299B69D4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/AJZS028" author="Debenham, ML" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology Supplementary Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B3" refString="Debenham, ML, 1974. A revision of the Australian and New Guinea predatory Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Nematocera) of the tribes Heteromyiini and Sphaeromiini. Australian Journal of Zoology Supplementary Series 22: 1 - 92" title="A revision of the Australian and New Guinea predatory Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Nematocera) of the tribes Heteromyiini and Sphaeromiini." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/AJZS028" volume="22" year="1974">Debenham (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="5B44F207A78254689600AAC98EB9BAE6" author="Wirth, WW" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="396 - 431" refId="B10" refString="Wirth, WW, Ratanaworabhan, NC, 1981. New species and records of predaceous midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae) from rice paddies in Thailand. Pacific Insects 23: 396 - 431" title="New species and records of predaceous midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae) from rice paddies in Thailand." volume="23" year="1981">Wirth and Ratanaworabhan (1981)</bibRefCitation>
. The only other species of 
<taxonomicName id="6530CA8A906C280330277ED3B754968F" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9353D14D6A9F915E81E8C6F26831851D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from mangrove forest is 
<taxonomicName id="5EDF70B3E2F0D3558354807BE7979D02" genus="N." lsidName="N. virago" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="virago">
<emphasis id="96B03F8BED113A0196BC2520CFA6AF89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. virago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Debenham which was recorded from many different habitats including a single female specimen collected from mangroves in Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="4481A3A39B9D085976F59B3CD1E2CC08" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/AJZS028" author="Debenham, ML" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology Supplementary Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B3" refString="Debenham, ML, 1974. A revision of the Australian and New Guinea predatory Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Nematocera) of the tribes Heteromyiini and Sphaeromiini. Australian Journal of Zoology Supplementary Series 22: 1 - 92" title="A revision of the Australian and New Guinea predatory Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Nematocera) of the tribes Heteromyiini and Sphaeromiini." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/AJZS028" volume="22" year="1974">Debenham 1974</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC464A00BCB10DA719B0735CCC1C7DB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName id="7354B511D1D9C9A85E833FE1845B2A42" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia bamenwana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="DF560774C6249DCA17CE8FB00CF77FFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to 
<taxonomicName id="F0F3EEE52638FAE2D3CEDAEFF2B48E7F" genus="N." lsidName="N. acanthopus" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="acanthopus">
<emphasis id="0EC2248CBCC3EFE2C050324E90B5B539" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. acanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Meijere) in the key to Southeast Asian species by 
<bibRefCitation id="7C0B3440B6FB42A17C9600D6D22EB1E0" author="Wirth, WW" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="396 - 431" refId="B10" refString="Wirth, WW, Ratanaworabhan, NC, 1981. New species and records of predaceous midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae) from rice paddies in Thailand. Pacific Insects 23: 396 - 431" title="New species and records of predaceous midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae) from rice paddies in Thailand." volume="23" year="1981">Wirth and Ratanaworabhan (1981)</bibRefCitation>
but in the latter species the forefemur and midfemur are entirely yellowish and the spermathecae are equal in size. India has 18 described species of 
<taxonomicName id="4366ACEC44C1CBAF7F99255CD91A83AE" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B9E4C4EA19C916AD348E9416E64599B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB34AF576E4884A21EFD965FC7F276DF" author="Mazumdar, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Monthly Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="131 - 151" refId="B7" refString="Mazumdar, A, Chaudhuri, PK, Das Gupta, SK, 2009. New insectivorous midges of the genus Nilobezzia Kieffer from India (Dipt., Ceratopogonidae: Sphaeromiini). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 145: 131 - 151" title="New insectivorous midges of the genus Nilobezzia Kieffer from India (Dipt., Ceratopogonidae: Sphaeromiini)." volume="145" year="2009">Mazumdar et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), some of which possess similar leg colour patterns and other characteristics to 
<taxonomicName id="4BA0100909D0E1A90514A1BBBE0F0AFF" genus="N." lsidName="N. bamenwana" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="49AC971DCDA2F26E3E5A396C0FDD604F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with wings shorter than 2.5 mm and significantly smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="19CADAB54215E7B59240CF1BC64F2417" genus="N." lsidName="N. bamenwana" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="3104A36A9686F7EE01E245F79D4D1587" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and none appear to be associated with mangroves. 
<taxonomicName id="363F9029928934713034E2C1589A9A27" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia bamenwana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="E4AA12BD2000A0FA3AE1C1298B9EC43D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to 
<taxonomicName id="7F591EC95BE652DDF06FB6B70054F442" genus="N." lsidName="N. opaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="opaca">
<emphasis id="3357F438B32866E69C31CDD5A878BE55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. opaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Das Gupta in the key by 
<bibRefCitation id="D708C1C24558B7899533651EED430074" author="Mazumdar, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Monthly Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="131 - 151" refId="B7" refString="Mazumdar, A, Chaudhuri, PK, Das Gupta, SK, 2009. New insectivorous midges of the genus Nilobezzia Kieffer from India (Dipt., Ceratopogonidae: Sphaeromiini). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 145: 131 - 151" title="New insectivorous midges of the genus Nilobezzia Kieffer from India (Dipt., Ceratopogonidae: Sphaeromiini)." volume="145" year="2009">Mazumdar et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, but that species can be distinguished by the obvious neck of spermathecae and legs excepting the midfemora, entirely brown. It runs to 
<taxonomicName id="A9D905EE095F3D4B8853AC780248EB74" genus="N." lsidName="N. formosana" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis id="C94298917BC8C9D077D05ED3DECEFA81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kieffer) in the key to Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName id="9EE7485050742AA38231D6D922FAB0B3" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC9687E46D22870EA820AC5E580D014" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="722E986AF1D45734E9ACE579C01DAF4B" author="Yu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Military Medical Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B12" refString="Yu, YX, Liu, JH, Liu, GP, Liu, ZJ, Hao, BS, Yan, G, Zhao, TS, 2005. Ceratopogonidae of China - Insecta, Diptera [in Chinese]. Military Medical Science Press, Beijing" title="Ceratopogonidae of China - Insecta, Diptera [in Chinese]." year="2005">Yu et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, but that species is much smaller in size with a wing length of only 2.11 mm. 
<taxonomicName id="631230AD28D7807CFC0205EBF4BFD731" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Nilobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilobezzia bamenwana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamenwana">
<emphasis id="F33084F83BCAD7B2B8F4B51C59532263" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Nilobezzia bamenwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is allied to 
<taxonomicName id="E2D46DF464EE0C2ABF2F833FF2C1C3C0" genus="N." lsidName="N. japana" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="japana">
<emphasis id="55021F3BEFC030D1CDC81F571EDAED23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N. japana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tokunaga in general colour, but the latter species is smaller (body length 3.2 mm), has more extensive dark markings on the forefemur and midfemur, and the foretibia lacks spines.
</paragraph>
